abstract: The establishment doesn’t have the credibility to stop the surging Sanders movement.
snippet: The establishment doesn’t have the credibility to stop the surging Sanders movement.
lead_paragraph: A half-hour before a Bernie Sanders rally on Saturday night in Iowa, a line snaked around the nearly 900-seat Ames City Auditorium, but no one else was being let in: The theater was full.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Monday the United States and China were in close contact regarding the newly identified coronavirus outbreak, which has infected thousands in more than 10 countries and killed at least 81.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Monday the United States and China were in close contact regarding the newly identified coronavirus outbreak, which has infected thousands in more than 10 countries and killed at least 81.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump said on Monday the United States and China were in close contact regarding the newly identified coronavirus outbreak, which has infected thousands in more than 10 countries and killed at least 81.
headline_main: Trump Says U.S., China in Close Contact on Coronavirus Outbreak
headline_print_headline: Trump Says U.S., China in Close Contact on Coronavirus Outbreak

abstract: Alan Dershowitz, a Harvard law professor, said he now believes that impeachable conduct must be criminal in nature, a departure from views he expressed in 1998.
snippet: Alan Dershowitz, a Harvard law professor, said he now believes that impeachable conduct must be criminal in nature, a departure from views he expressed in 1998.
lead_paragraph: Alan Dershowitz, a Harvard law professor, said he now believes that impeachable conduct must be criminal in nature. But even if that weren’t so, he said, the charges against Mr. Trump — abuse of power and obstruction of justice — are simply too ill-defined to accept as violations worthy of impeachment.
headline_main: Dershowitz makes the case that the charges against Trump are too vague.

abstract: The former national security adviser shared his unease with the attorney general, who cited his own worries about the president’s conversations with the leaders of Turkey and China.
snippet: The former national security adviser shared his unease with the attorney general, who cited his own worries about the president’s conversations with the leaders of Turkey and China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — John R. Bolton, the former national security adviser, privately told Attorney General William P. Barr last year that he had concerns that President Trump was effectively granting personal favors to the autocratic leaders of Turkey and China, according to an unpublished manuscript by Mr. Bolton.

abstract: When the San Francisco 49ers and Kansas City Chiefs face off at the National Football League's Super Bowl LIV in Miami on Sunday, billionaire presidential candidates will battle for attention while big brands bearing positive messages hope to bring balance to the divisive political atmosphere.
snippet: When the San Francisco 49ers and Kansas City Chiefs face off at the National Football League's Super Bowl LIV in Miami on Sunday, billionaire presidential candidates will battle for attention while big brands bearing positive messages hope to brin...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - When the San Francisco 49ers and Kansas City Chiefs face off at the National Football League's Super Bowl LIV in Miami on Sunday, billionaire presidential candidates will battle for attention while big brands bearing positive messages hope to bring balance to the divisive political atmosphere.
headline_main: Super Bowl to Feature Trump, Bloomberg and Corporate America Battling for Attention
headline_print_headline: Super Bowl to Feature Trump, Bloomberg and Corporate America Battling for Attention

abstract: After a day of somewhat monotonous legal arguments, it is no surprise that President Trump’s legal team saved its star consultant for a time when many Americans are tuning in.
snippet: After a day of somewhat monotonous legal arguments, it is no surprise that President Trump’s legal team saved its star consultant for a time when many Americans are tuning in.
lead_paragraph: After a day of somewhat monotonous legal arguments, it is no surprise that President Trump’s legal team saved its star consultant — Professor Alan Dershowitz of Harvard Law School — for the 8 p.m. hour, prime time on national television.

abstract: President Donald Trump's defense relies in part on arguments made in the impeachment trial of President Andrew Johnson more than 150 years ago: that impeachment requires a crime.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's defense relies in part on arguments made in the impeachment trial of President Andrew Johnson more than 150 years ago: that impeachment requires a crime.

abstract: Representative Doug Collins is expected to announce his campaign on Tuesday, setting up a brutal Republican-on-Republican fight.
snippet: Representative Doug Collins is expected to announce his campaign on Tuesday, setting up a brutal Republican-on-Republican fight.
lead_paragraph: Representative Doug Collins, one of the faces of President Trump’s impeachment defense, plans to challenge Senator Kelly Loeffler in this fall’s special election for one of Georgia’s Senate seats, people familiar with his plans said on Monday.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump's Senate impeachment trial was overshadowed on Monday by an unpublished manuscript from former national security adviser John Bolton that said Trump wanted to freeze U.S. aid to Ukraine to pressure the country for politically beneficial investigations.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump's Senate impeachment trial was overshadowed on Monday by an unpublished manuscript from former national security adviser John Bolton that said Trump wanted to freeze U.S. aid to Ukraine to pressure the country for politically beneficial investigations.
